newFindings[20]{id,severity,area,agent,description,suggestedAction}:
  N-01,blocking,wizard-installer-wiring,feature-coverage-agent,"Phase 8 wizard writes skills/<name>/SKILL.md to repo but installer writes to ~/.claude/skills/<name>/SKILL.md. These are different paths; wizard does not invoke installer. AC restart notice says 'restart your Claude Code session' implying skill is active but ~/.claude/skills/ is empty. First-time author hits broken activation experience.","Add to Phase 8 wizard completion output: either auto-invoke /loom-library use <name> OR print explicit instruction 'Run /loom-library use <name> to install the skill to ~/.claude/skills/'. Add as AC."
  N-02,blocking,ownership-conflict,parallelization-agent,"Phase 0b AC requires CLAUDE.md ### Authoring Resources sub-section with full resource-type decision tree (line 778). Phase 11 AC independently requires grep returns exactly one ### Authoring Resources heading (line 1577). Both phases own CLAUDE.md. One will be marked red.","Disambiguate: either (a) Phase 0b writes stub (heading + placeholder), relax AC to 'sub-section heading exists'; Phase 11 fills content; OR (b) Phase 0b writes full sub-section, narrow Phase 11 to confirming-presence + wizard-references only."
  N-03,blocking,wizard-ux,ux-agent,"Phase 8 wizard has no escape hatch if user picks wrong trigger-vs-description-activated option at step 3. Only recovery is re-running the wizard which conflicts on existing library.yaml entry. No idempotency guarantee specified for the wizard when target skill name already exists.","Add to Phase 8 AC: (a) idempotency — if target skill name exists in library.yaml, wizard MUST detect conflict and offer overwrite/abort; (b) step-correction escape — wizard confirms choice before writing any files so user can answer N to go back."
  N-04,blocking,ambiguous-prompt-undefined,ux-agent,"Phase 9 /loom-library add heuristic specifies 'ambiguous → prompt user to choose type explicitly' but prompt copy is undefined. User who doesn't know protocol-vs-skill distinction sees an unspecified prompt with no in-context explanation. AC verifies prompt fires (S-28) but not that prompt is informative.","Phase 9 spec must inline the prompt copy. Required: prompt names both options with one-sentence explanation of distinction (e.g. 'skill: activates automatically on matching file patterns via Claude Code; protocol: inter-agent message schema used by Loom orchestration'). Add as AC."
  N-05,blocking,cross-wave-layering,parallelization-agent,"Phase 9 modifies commands/loom-library.md but only declares Phase 0 and Phase 3 as dependencies. Phase 7 (which also runs in Wave 4 with smoke tests) reads the live file. If Phase 9 runs before Phase 7's full-suite gate, layering may operate on incomplete Phase 3 baseline. No precondition check asserts Phase 3 changes are in place.","Add Phase 7 to Phase 9 Dependencies (or sequence Phase 9 after Phase 7 within Wave 4). Add precondition AC: grep -n 'NOT_IN_CATALOG' commands/loom-library.md must return ≥1 line before Phase 9 edits begin."
  N-06,warning,partial-resolve-F007,ux-agent,"F-007 NOT_IN_CATALOG message text is present and correct but envelope structure spec only shows TOON block for SOURCE_VALIDATION_ERROR. NOT_IN_CATALOG appears as bare string with no surrounding envelope definition. User sees flat message with no structured context fields (e.g. checkedName, suggestedCommand).","Add minimal TOON envelope example for NOT_IN_CATALOG parallel to SOURCE_VALIDATION_ERROR. Include checkedName and suggestedCommand fields in details block."
  N-07,warning,heuristic-classification,feature-coverage-agent,"Phase 9 heuristic uses SKILL.md filename presence as primary signal for type:skill classification. But SkillEntry schema allows source to be any relative repo path. A skill whose source file is named python-conventions.md (not SKILL.md) would be misclassified. Inverse also possible.","Phase 9 heuristic must prioritize triggers: frontmatter presence over filename. Add AC for the case where source filename differs from SKILL.md."
  N-08,warning,phase-9-no-readguard,feature-coverage-agent,"Phase 9 has no read-guard in AC asserting commands/loom-library.md already contains Phase 3 changes (skill routing, NOT_IN_CATALOG error block). Re-spawned Wave 4 agent reading stale baseline could overwrite Phase 3 work.","Add to Phase 9 AC: precondition check grep -n 'NOT_IN_CATALOG' commands/loom-library.md returns ≥1 line. Makes Phase 3→Phase 9 layering enforcement explicit and machine-verifiable."
  N-09,warning,spurious-dependency,phasing-agent,"Phase 4 declares Phase 3 as dependency but all tests import from hooks/lib/skill-router.ts (Phase 0 artifact) and test only pure functions. Phase 3 dependency is pre-F-005 remnant. Blocks full Wave 2 parallelism.","Remove Phase 3 from Phase 4 Dependencies list. Phase 4 needs only Phase 0. Allows Phase 3 4 5 to run fully in parallel within Wave 2."
  N-10,warning,missing-dependency,phasing-agent,"Phase 9 declares Phase 0 and Phase 3 dependencies but not Phase 5. Heuristic must distinguish SKILL.md + triggers: from protocol files. Phase 5 is where the canonical SKILL.md format is established. Phase 3 teaches installer to install skills but doesn't define what SKILL.md looks like.","Add Phase 5 to Phase 9 Dependencies list."
  N-11,warning,no-wave-4-gate,phasing-agent,"Wave 0 has wave-0-gate.toon (tsc). Wave 1 has wave-1-gate.toon (bun test + tsc). Wave 4's de facto gate is Phase 7's bun test full suite but it covers only Phases 1-6 outputs. Phases 8-11 have only grep-based ACs with no test-level catch.","Add Wave 4 exit gate artifact .plan-execution/stage-context/wave-4-gate.toon to Phase 7. Extend Phase 7 AC to include the authoring scaffolding grep checks. If Phase 7 truly runs parallel with 8-11 add a Phase 12 (Wave 5) for the gate."
  N-12,warning,sequencing-inversion,phasing-agent,"Phase 7 runs in parallel with Phases 8-11 but conceptually should gate them. If Phase 7 fails indicating Phases 1-6 are broken Phases 8-11 still proceed and write scaffolding referencing broken foundations.","Either (a) make Phases 8-11 depend on Phase 7 (demoting from parallel to sequential after Phase 7) OR (b) move Phases 8-11 to Wave 5."
  N-13,warning,phase-0-instruction-density,agentic-workflow-agent,"Phase 0 has 14 ACs + CURRENT_VERSION trap (must NOT bump) + read-only constraint + audit obligation. Constraint appears only as inline comment and one AC buried in list. Agent has meaningful probability of missing the CURRENT_VERSION constraint or conflating stub with real impl.","Add prominent DO NOT bump CURRENT_VERSION in this phase callout box at top of Phase 0 deliverables table. Or split Phase 0 into 0a (interfaces + fixtures + audit) and 0b-type (skill-router.ts authoring)."
  N-14,warning,missing-dependency,agentic-workflow-agent,"Phase 8 wizard needs to read protocols/kit.schema.md (updated in Phase 6) for typed includes: format to generate skill:<name> entries. Phase 8 declares Phase 0 Phase 3 Phase 5 but NOT Phase 6.","Add Phase 6 to Phase 8 Dependencies list. Add Read inputs note naming protocols/kit.schema.md as required read."
  N-15,warning,wizard-non-idempotent,agentic-workflow-agent,"Phase 8 wizard step 6 writes to skills/library.yaml. If agent crashes after library.yaml write but before wizard file completes catalog has dangling skill registration pointing at nonexistent SKILL.md. On re-run agent appends second copy violating uq_library_skills_name index.","Add to Phase 8 AC: if library.skills: entry for named skill already exists wizard prints warning and skips duplicate append. Mirrors existing uq_library_skills_name constraint already in schema table."
  N-16,warning,stage-context-gaps,agentic-workflow-agent,"F-014 applied but Wave 4 Phases 8 9 11 have NO stage-context writes. Phase 8 is load-bearing (Phases 10 and 11 read its output) but downstream agents must cold-read commands/loom-skill.md to understand wizard.","Add phase-8.toon phase-9.toon phase-11.toon to respective deliverables tables. phase-8.toon records: wizard file path, interview steps confirmed, library.yaml write confirmed, restart-notice confirmed."
  N-17,warning,wave-4-illusion,parallelization-agent,"Wave 4 advertises 5 parallel phases but dependency graph serializes most. Phase 8 truly parallel. Phase 9 truly parallel (after F-N05 added Phase 7 dep). Phase 10 depends on Phase 8 — serializes behind it. Phase 11 depends on Phase 10. Actual structure: 3-wide fan (7, 8, 9) + 2-phase serial tail (8→10→11).","Redraw Wave 4 internal structure. Label sub-waves: Wave 4a = {Phase 7, Phase 8, Phase 9} parallel; Wave 4b = {Phase 10, Phase 11} serial after Phase 8. Add Wave 4a→4b gate confirming commands/loom-skill.md exists."
  N-18,warning,milestone-collapse,strategy-agent,"M-02 (python-conventions + schema docs) and M-03 (authoring scaffolding) both declared 'End of Wave 4'. Collapses two distinct milestone completions into one wave boundary. If any Phase 8-11 item slips M-02 cannot be declared done. PLAN-oss-launch.md may depend on M-02 not M-03 — blocked unnecessarily.","Rename milestone declarations: M-02 = End of Phase 7. M-03 = End of Phase 11. Document they may run concurrently if phases are independent."
  N-19,warning,oss-launch-dep,strategy-agent,"Plan grown to 13 phases — milestone-scale. Owns CLAUDE.md README.md library.yaml loom-library.md loom-upgrade.md loom-skill.md (new) loom-agent.md change-proposal.schema.md kit.schema.md plus full migrator + test surface. PLAN-oss-launch.md dependency unclear.","Before execution: confirm PLAN-oss-launch.md dependency on M-02/M-03. Declare merge order explicitly in both plans. Lock decision: 'OSS launch is blocked until this merges' or 'OSS launch can ship independently'."
  N-20,warning,decision-tree-weakspec,ux-agent,"Phase 11 decision tree spec'd as 'expressed as list or table (not prose only)' but actual content is one line of prose per type in deliverables table. Implementer writing 'agent — orchestrates work' as single-column list has technically satisfied AC but produced document with no guidance on WHEN to reach for each type.","Strengthen Phase 11 AC to require two-column structure: column 1 = resource type name; column 2 = 'use when' trigger condition as question or condition. Example: 'skill | Use when you want domain conventions applied automatically whenever matching files are open.'"

infoFindings[5]{id,severity,area,agent,description}:
  N-21,info,phase-0-cohesion,phasing-agent,"skills/library.yaml v4 bump is runtime data migration not contract definition. Could move to Phase 1 alongside CURRENT_VERSION bump for better cohesion. Low priority cleanup."
  N-22,info,end-to-end-flow,ux-agent,"End-to-end kit-author flow (read CLAUDE.md → install python-conventions → author own skill) described in fragments across Phase 0b and Phases 8-11. No single touchpoint stitches them. Add pointer in Phase 0b CLAUDE.md to /loom-skill create."
  N-23,info,wave-0-gate-writer,parallelization-agent,"wave-0-gate.toon has single-writer ambiguity. No phase explicitly owns the gate artifact. If Phase 0b finishes first and writes gate file prematurely Phase 0's tsc check may not yet pass.","Assign wave-0-gate.toon to orchestrator post-Wave-0 step OR add Phase 0 dependency to Phase 0b."
  N-24,info,criteria-naming,feature-coverage-agent,"criteria-plan.toon line 20 C-10 name still says components[] but body says items[]. Pre-existing naming inconsistency not cleaned up in review integration. Doesn't block (verifier uses body) but produces confusing test failure message."
  N-25,info,positioning-audience,strategy-agent,"Plan adds /loom-skill create implying third audience (third-party authors). README positioning paragraph (Phase 0b) addresses platform-evaluators only. Add one sentence distinguishing 'use a skill kit' from 'author a skill kit'."

